text:
Can I help you
with something?
Oh, no, no!

I'm good!
All good!

Are you looking for something
for your girlfriend

or your mother?
Oh, hell, no.

Everything in this store
is too expensive, man.

I take my mother
up to Rainbows.

You know, there, I can get
some drawers, a blouse,
and a durag for $5.

Sir, are you spying
on those customers?

I'm trying to, but you keep
on interrupting me!

I'm afraid I'm gonna have to
ask you to leave, sir.

And I'm afraid I'm gonna have to
ask you to make me, sir.

Okay.
Security!

I ain't scared of no toy cops.
You understand me?

I'm Big Tray
from the Group Home!

Brooklyn!
You understand?

Get down
from my ground!

You know, Bed-Stuy, do or die,
take the girl, kill the guy.

You know, what -- what --
what you say,

that door was down
here on the right?
Mm-hmm.

Oh, I'm gonna go down this way,
okay?
Please don't handle me rough.

Treat me
like I'm with child.

See? Look!
See? Look!
Oh, I'm going into labor!
This baby keep on kicking!

You know what I'm saying?
Treat me like that.

You don't have to treat me
so rough.

I know where the door is.
You don't got to follow me.

Alright, man.
Alright!
